[2026-03-18T18:40:16.449Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Lk8grJUncn6p1N17Nc5p84","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Token Lifecycle Audit Events\n\n**7 new audit event types** added to the discriminated union in `auditLog.ts`:\n\n| Action | When emitted |\n|---|---|\n| `oauth:authorize` | OAuth authorization URL generated |\n| `oauth:exchange` | Authorization code exchanged for tokens |\n| `oauth:refresh` | Token successfully refreshed (API or auto) |\n| `oauth:refresh_failed` | Token refresh failed (API or auto) |\n| `oauth:disconnect` | Tokens revoked and cleared |\n| `token:inject` | Direct API key set via `POST /api/token` |\n| `token:expiring_soon` | Token within configurable warning threshold |\n\n**Files changed:**\n\n- **`auditLog.ts`** — 7 new entry interfaces added to the `AuditEntry` union\n- **`config.ts`** — New `tokenExpiryWarningMinutes` config (env: `TOKEN_EXPIRY_WARNING_MINUTES`, default: 30)\n- **`oauthHttpHandlers.ts`** — Accepts optional `AuditLog`, emits audit events for authorize, exchange, refresh, refresh_failed, disconnect, and token inject\n- **`httpApi.ts`** — Passes `auditLog` through to `handleOAuthRoute`\n- **`oauth.ts`** — `setAuditLog()` method for wiring; `getValidAccessToken()` emits `token:expiring_soon` once per token cycle; `executeRefresh()` emits `oauth:refresh` / `oauth:refresh_failed` for auto-refresh path\n- **`index.ts`** — Wires `oauth.setAuditLog(auditLog, config.tokenExpiryWarningMinutes)` at startup\n\nAll events are queryable via the existing `GET /api/admin/audit?action=oauth:exchange` endpoint."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":362,"cache_read_input_tokens":73225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":362},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_availab